						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Maybe this wouldn't be nearly as confusing if you guys would stop talking about "CPU memory". This doesn't make any sense - the CPU is a chip that fetches instructions from other memory chips (internal RAM, SRAM, PRG-ROM).</div>
<br />Come on Bregalad, we have always used the terms "CPU memory" to talk about the memory that the CPU sees and "PPU memory" to talk about the memory that the PPU sees. We also talk about "palette memory" and such, because they are separate memories. We could also use WRAM and VRAM, but we must be able to identify them as separate memories.</div>

